result.name: Passion by Gerard Dubois

reviews.text: The food is usually really good here, same at all the other ones of this chain. The fun bit is the totally hapharzard service. It’s usually the only place round here to get a seat a lunch. You need some patience; it’s generally all in good humour!

I have to say the food is delicious. The staff is super kind and very sweet despite the customers being mean. It would be nice if there was more than one person at the counter and I felt so bad that customers were being mean to the one person that worked there.

I hope the lady behind the counter knows she is absolutely delightful and handled those horrible customers so well. She served us with a smile even though everyone was giving her a hard time for it being busy and she’s the only one!

Had the Foret Noire (similar to blackforest cake) and it was good, cappuccino was good too.
I won't give 5 stars because of the staff, they were not helpful and impatient!
Very tasty salads, but there were not enough choices of drinks.
Attractive scones, bread, salads, pizzas and spaghetti menu. Comfortable place to sit and self served. I like this place.

result.name: Cityplaza

reviews.text:
Many different stores for people to buy stuff from. There's an ice skating rink and many people go there to play.

The mall is close to the MTR station, which makes it very convenient to reach. There is also a park nearby.

This was the biggest mall I ever visited. Free wifi. Public transport right outside the main entrance doors. Everything you need under one roof. Restaurants around every corner so you can't go wrong. Will definitely go back.

Shopping here is not for the faint of heart. Fill thy wallet and endure queues of long.
From left and to right, shall your eyes dart.
Your purchases a burden, arms strong.

The food court has a variety of Japanese related food items and it is all delicious and fast delivery. The food quality matches the food prices. Only issue is it gets very crowded during lunch hours other than that, a great experience.

This is now a very large mall after its extension. Not only it is big where you could almost get anything what other malls offer, it is also very spacious without the crazy crowds(yet) probably due to its location which is still very much an residential area. Though slightly off the shopping belt, it is very easily accessible by the MTR.
